      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) holds current ISO 9001 certification; FDA-internal solver instance subject to 21 CFR Part 820 software controls. Version control and audit trail documented.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA environments used in the ensemble (FDA in-house, Ansys commercial, DePuy Synthes internal) operate under documented software quality management systems. Version identifiers recorded in the simulation logbook. Gradation 2 required and achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems (NAFEMS LE1, LE10) reproduced to within 0.5% of analytical solution. Patch test passed for all element types employed.",
      "rationale": "Standard NAFEMS linear-elastic benchmarks were executed in each solver environment. All results within tolerance. Element formulations (SOLID186 hexahedral, CONTA174 contact) are well-established in literature for metallic implant simulation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Global Richardson extrapolation GCI < 2% for all three QoIs; local stress convergence within 5% at screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh densities (coarse ~180k, medium ~540k, fine ~1.6M elements) evaluated. GCI for stiffness: 0.8%; yield force: 1.4%; force at 40 mm: 1.1%. Local contact stress convergence confirmed at fine density. Medium mesh adopted for production runs balancing accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual force norm < 1e-4 N at each converged load step; energy criterion < 1e-6.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses employed full Newton-Raphson with line search. Convergence criteria tightened relative to solver defaults. All 11 simulation cases converged without bisection failure. Residual norms logged and archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in original build; checklist covering boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application verified.",
      "rationale": "A second qualified FEA analyst performed an independent review of all model inputs, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts prior to result extraction. Discrepancies identified in initial contact offset settings were corrected before final runs. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model (bilinear isotropic hardening) appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static loading; geometric nonlinearity (large deformation) enabled; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian.",
      "rationale": "The bilinear isotropic hardening model captures the dominant post-yield behavior observed in tensile coupon data for Ti-6Al-4V (ASTM E8). Geometric nonlinearity is necessary given 40 mm crosshead displacement relative to ~100 mm gauge length. Frictional contact (μ = 0.2) at screw-rod interface consistent with published values. Model form judged adequate for the QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (E, yield stress, tangent modulus) sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of production screws; uncertainty in inputs propagated via Monte Carlo (n=1000).",
      "rationale": "Lot-specific Ti-6Al-4V tensile data (n=5 coupons per lot) provided E = 114 ± 3 GPa, σ_y = 880 ± 15 MPa. CMM-measured screw geometry used to build nominal CAD. Input uncertainty propagated; resulting output uncertainty bands incorporated into E/uval calculation. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing; samples span two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested: 6 at Laboratory A (FDA), 5 at Laboratory B (DePuy Synthes). All constructs dimensionally inspected by CMM prior to testing. Lot traceability documented. Inter-laboratory variability assessed; CV < 4% for stiffness. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two loading rates and two environmental temperatures to characterize sensitivity; full ASTM F1717 protocol compliance.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single displacement rate (1 mm/min) and single ambient temperature (22 °C) per ASTM F1717. While the standard specifies these conditions, no parametric variation of loading rate or temperature was performed. This limits the ability to characterize model sensitivity to those variables. Gradation 2 achieved against a required Gradation 3; this is the identified below-threshold factor. Risk accepted given the quasi-static, ambient nature of the intended use."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to physical test fixture constraints; applied displacement profile matches machine crosshead motion log.",
      "rationale": "Physical fixture constrains the inferior vertebral body block in all six DOF; superior block loaded in axial compression with 5° anterior angulation per F1717. FEA replicates this via fixed support at inferior block reference point and prescribed displacement at superior block. Crosshead displacement logs from both labs used to define load-step sequence. Equivalency confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: predicted 487 N/mm vs. experimental 501 ± 18 N/mm; difference 2.8%; E/uval = 1.41. Yield force: predicted 1243 N vs. 1329 ± 47 N; difference 6.5%; E/uval = 1.18. Force at 40 mm: predicted 1876 N vs. 2062 ± 61 N; difference 9.0%; E/uval = 1.63. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical decision context and are the primary outputs cited in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness characterizes load-sharing with the vertebral column; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation relevant to implant integrity; force at 40 mm is the ASTM F1717 standard reporting metric. All three QoIs are explicitly cited in the 510(k) predicate comparison. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717 bench test, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, static compression-bending) is the same scenario as the COU; no extrapolation required.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity is identical to the COU: same device (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), same test standard (ASTM F1717), same loading mode (static compression-bending), same QoIs. No domain transfer or interpolation is required. The validation evidence directly supports the credibility claim. Gradation 3 achieved."
    }
